  "prompt": "What is the best free webDAV service?",
  "response": "Several free WebDAV services are available, and the best choice will depend on your specific needs, such as storage capacity, ease of use, and features. Here are a few popular options you might consider:\n\n1. **Google Drive with WebDAV Support**: While Google Drive itself does not natively support WebDAV, you can use third-party applications and tools like \"rclone\" to create a WebDAV-compatible connection.\n\n2. **Dropbox**: Similar to Google Drive, Dropbox doesn't offer direct WebDAV support, but you can use tools to set up a WebDAV connection.\n\n3. **ownCloud**: This is a self-hosted solution that offers WebDAV support. You can host it on your server, or some providers offer free plans.\n\n4. **Nextcloud**: Like ownCloud, Nextcloud is a self-hosted platform that supports WebDAV. Hosting it is usually free if you set it up on your server.\n\n5. **Cozy Cloud**: Cozy offers personal cloud storage with WebDAV support. It has a free tier with limited storage.\n\n6. **pCloud**: pCloud offers a free tier for storage and allows access via WebDAV through its paid plans.\n\n7. **FileRun**: This is another self-hosted option that supports WebDAV and has a free version with limited features.\n\nWhen choosing a service, consider factors like data privacy, file synchronization features, and the ease of setting up integrations. Make sure to check the terms of service and storage limits for any free plan.",
